December 18, 2004 • Howard Tayler

My last entry was written shortly after renting Fable for the XBox. I spent around $6.00 on the rental, which isn't too bad.

Then I spent around 24 hours during the week playing the game that WAS bad.

Symptoms of the opportunity cost of gaming: the house is more cluttered, the dishes haven't been done consistently, the buffer has slipped a few days, and the entry hasn't been updated.

The game went back to Blockbuster this morning
